## Decisions Made
- Use function argument instead of env var for changeset bypass: An env var can be set by any external caller, defeating the guard. A positional argument is only passable by internal callers (changeset_apply -> pipeline_insert -> assert_not_batch_branch).

## Problems Encountered
- CodeRabbit flagged that _KD_VIA_CHANGESET_APPLY is externally controllable: Resolved by replacing the env var check with a local function parameter passed through the internal call chain.

## Constraints Identified
- Batch-branch guard bypass must be internal-only: External callers must never be able to skip the guard, so the sentinel mechanism must not be reachable from the process environment.

